The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for tracking multiple faces in egocentric photo streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for tracking and grouping similar tracklets, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed method, which involves the use of confidence measures, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also deals with the analysis of social events, which involves human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques for detecting and tracking faces, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
